.START 

West German retail sales were up a real, or price-adjusted, 4% in August from August 1988, the Federal Statistics Office said. 

The statistics office also said nominal sales rose 6.5% from a year ago.
In July, real sales fell 0.2% from a year earlier and nominal sales rose 2.6%. 

The statistics office pointed out that 11 days of summer clearance sales occurred in the month of August 1989, while in 1988, only six days of summer clearance occurred in August and the rest in July. 

Between January and August, retail sales rose a real 2.5% and were up a nominal 5.1% from the year-earlier period. 

